Mon, 15 Feb 2021 20:29:25 +0100
Matthias von Faber

Windows: Replace fopen() with std::filebuf, remove UTF-8 hack

With the removal of this hack, fopen() can now only see ASCII paths on
Windows since it expects ANSI and Surge strings are UTF-8. Use C++ API
that takes an fs::path instead (std::filebuf, std::fstream).
